ta-pf-type="Image" class="sc-fHeRUh frnBmr pf-150_"><img src="https://cdn.shopify.com/s/files/1/0069/6470/7389/t/9/assets/pf-4102079d--image-3_1200x.jpg?v=1626387852" srcSet="https://cdn.shopify.com/s/files/1/0069/6470/7389/t/9/assets/pf-4102079d--image-3.jpg?v=1626387852 1536w" sizes="(min-width: 1536px) 1536px, (min-width: 1024px) 1280px, (min-width: 640px) 768px, 320px" loading="lazy"/></a></div></div></div><div class="sc-hiCibw hHrFfF pf-151_ pf-r pf-r-eh" style="--s-xs:15px" data-pf-type="Row"><div class="pf-c" style="--c-xs:12;--c-lg:12"><div data-pf-type="Column" class="sc-hAcGzb bAQARH pf-152_"><p class="sc-fmBCVi laenLa pf-153_" data-pf-type="Paragraph"><span data-pf-type="Text" class="sc-jtXEFf kGfXVs pf-155_">Hair Curlers come in all shapes and sizes, depending on the curl size you want and on your hair length/thickness will determine the size of wand you need. For very short hair a smaller sized Barrell would be better as you might struggle to get the hair neatly wrapped round a large tong. For long hair a thin barrel will give you tight curls, if you are looking for a looser wavy style then choose a large or wide barrel shape. Our favourite is the GHD Curve Soft Curl Tong, the size is perfect for big bouncy curls and with a maximum temperature of 185 degrees its perfectly safe for use with <a href="https://www.cliphair.co.uk/" target="_blank">hair extensions.&nbsp;</a></span></p></div></div></div><div class="sc-hiCibw hHrFfF pf-156_ pf-r pf-r-eh" style="--s-xs:15px" data-pf-type="Row"><div class="pf-c" style="--c-xs:12;--c-lg:12"><div data-pf-type="Column" class="sc-hAcGzb bAQARH pf-157_"><h3 data-pf-type="Heading" id="hairstraightners" class="sc-ctqQKy ioCblW pf-158_"><span data-pf-type="Text" class="sc-jtXEFf kGfXVs pf-160_">Hair Straighteners&nbsp;</span></h3><div class="sc-hiCibw hHrFfF pf-161_ pf-r pf-r-eh" style="--s-xs:15px" data-pf-type="Row"><div class="pf-c" style="--c-xs:12;--c-lg:12"><div data-pf-type="Column" class="sc-hAcGzb bAQARH pf-162_